# Automated Smoke Tests for DataArt.com

This repository contains automated smoke tests for DataArt's website (https://www.dataart.com/). The smoke tests aim to validate the basic functionality and key features of the website using the Robot Framework.

## Prerequisites

To execute the smoke tests, you need to have the following installed:

- Python (version 3.x)
- Robot Framework (latest version)
- SeleniumLibrary (latest version)

You can install the `robotframework-seleniumlibrary` using the following command:
pip install robotframework-seleniumlibrary


Additionally, you need to install the `Intellibot` plugin for better Robot Framework integration in your preferred IDE.


## Running the Tests

To run the smoke tests, follow these steps:

1. Open your preferred IDE or command-line interface.
2. Navigate to the root directory.
3. Execute the following command:
   robot -d results .\Tests


This command will run all the tests located in the `Tests` directory and generate the test results in the `results` directory.

Please note that you can customize the test execution and output directory according to your needs.

## Test Scenarios

1. Navigating to Main Pages and External Links:
   - Validates that the main pages of the website can be accessed.
   - Verifies that external links, such as social media profiles, are functional.

2. Contact Us Form:
   - Automates the process of filling in the contact us form.
   - Validates that the form submission is successful.








